{
  "doc_id": "26932",
  "text": "Fractal view of physiology has become the basis in understanding and controlling physiological networks where both homeostatic and allometric control mechanisms existed [CITATION_1] . Homeostatic control has a negative feedback character which is local and rapid while allometric control can take into account long-range interactions in complex phenomena [CITATION_2] . Hence, in recent modeling the dynamics and control of complex physiological phenomena the fractional calculus is more frequently applied [CITATION_3] . Furthermore, there have been efforts of reconstructing the network between physiological processes when some physiological signals are not observed yet capturing their fractional behavior through fractional order derivatives [CITATION_4] .",
